{"word":"ἀγριέλαιος","slug":"ἀγριέλαιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀγριέλαιος, ου, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἄγριος\">ἄγριος</a>, ἔλαιος</el>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ opp.\">opp.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:καλλιέλαιος\">καλλιέλαιος</a></el>; apparently formed as noun from the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀγριέλαιος\">ἀγριέλαιος</a>, ον</el>, ‘of wild olive’; in Greek, trees are ordinarily feminine: <b><i>wild olive tree</i> <a href='B:520 11:17'>Ro 11:17</a>, <a href='B:520 11:24'>24</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀγρεύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἄγριος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}